name: Léda et le Cygne #2
description:
Collection Leda and the Swan. 
According to the myth, Leda, the Queen of Sparta was one of the great loves of Zeus. He came to her in the form of a swan and seduced her while she bathed by a river. 
Based on an original work from Paul Cézanne and reinterpreted with AI.
[August 2021]
